[Rules]
1. Use the **name labels** on the rendered image to identify objects — don't guess
2. Use the **Object Layout Table** for precise current positions — don't estimate from pixels
3. Position accuracy is the MOST IMPORTANT factor
4. Adjacent/touching furniture is NORMAL arrangement, not overlap
5. Provide approximate suggested coordinates for position fixes when possible
6. overall_score: 0.0 (completely wrong layout) to 1.0 (perfect match)
7. is_acceptable: true only when major positions are correct and no serious overlaps
8. Output ONLY valid JSON, no explanations or commentary
9. **Walls are NOT in the layout table.** Both entries of every `overlapping_pairs` item MUST be names that literally appear in the Object Layout Table. Any pair mentioning "wall", "North/South/East/West Wall", "floor", "ceiling", "window", or any architectural element is INVALID and will be rejected. Use `out_of_bounds` (with clear visual evidence only) if you truly believe a furniture item is outside the room.
